sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as Client<br/>(UI / Python SDK / curl)
    participant Gateway as Kubeflow Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Proxy as model-registry (proxy)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Istio mTLS
    participant DB as MySQL/PostgreSQL<br/>3306/5432/TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as controller-manager<br/>8081/TCP (health)
    participant KServePod as KServe Pod<br/>(init container)
    participant CSI as mr-storage-initializer
    participant AsyncJob as async-upload job<br/>(Python)
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Sigstore as Sigstore/Rekor<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: Model Registration via REST API
        Client->>Gateway: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
        Gateway->>Proxy: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8080, Istio mTLS (ISTIO_MUTUAL)
        Proxy->>DB: INSERT model metadata<br/>TCP 3306/5432, Optional TLS<br/>Auth: username/password
        DB-->>Proxy: Query result
        Proxy-->>Gateway: 201 Created (JSON)
        Gateway-->>Client: Response
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over K8sAPI,Controller: Flow 2: InferenceService Sync (Controller)
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: InferenceService created/updated<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>Proxy: POST/PATCH serving_environments, inference_services<br/>HTTP/8080, InsecureSkipVerify=true<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        Proxy->>DB: Upsert metadata<br/>TCP 3306/5432
        DB-->>Proxy: Result
        Proxy-->>Controller: 200 OK
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over KServePod,S3: Flow 3: KServe Model Download (CSI Initializer)
        KServePod->>CSI: Init container starts<br/>model-registry://model/version URI
        CSI->>Proxy: GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/model_artifacts/{id}<br/>HTTP/8080, No Auth
        Proxy->>DB: Query artifact<br/>TCP 3306/5432
        DB-->>Proxy: Artifact with storage URI
        Proxy-->>CSI: Artifact response (s3://bucket/path)
        CSI->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Provider-specific (AWS IAM)
        S3-->>CSI: Model files
        CSI-->>KServePod: Model ready at /mnt/models/
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 255)
        Note over AsyncJob,Sigstore: Flow 4: Async Model Upload Job
        AsyncJob->>S3: Download model from source<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM credentials
        S3-->>AsyncJob: Model files
        AsyncJob->>OCI: Push model image (skopeo/olot)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: username/password
        OCI-->>AsyncJob: Push complete
        AsyncJob->>Sigstore: Sign model/image (optional)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OIDC identity token
        Sigstore-->>AsyncJob: Signature recorded
        AsyncJob->>Proxy: Register/update metadata<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
        Proxy->>DB: Upsert artifact URI<br/>TCP 3306/5432
        DB-->>Proxy: Result
        Proxy-->>AsyncJob: 200 OK
    end
